modules.description: Tracks counts of elements with increment and initialization capabilities. Operates on a custom type representing a mapping from elements to counts. Initializes a counter, increments specific elements, and constructs counters from sequences of element-count pairs.

Constructs a relation from a size parameter or a sequence of key-value pairs, supporting lookups and membership checks. Operates on tuples of keys and values, storing associated lists of values per key. Used to model one-to-many mappings in graph traversal and data indexing scenarios.

Counts occurrences of elements and organizes them into grouped structures. Works with lists of arbitrary values and returns associations mapping elements to their frequencies or grouped lists. Used to generate histograms from raw data or categorize items for analysis.

Maintains a mapping from elements to aggregated values, supporting both counting and relational lookups. It handles operations like incrementing counts, building associations between keys and multiple values, and retrieving summaries. Users can initialize structures from sequences, query bin contents, and manage data in a flexible, histogram-like format. Examples include tracking frequency distributions or building adjacency lists for graph processing.
